- Let's denote $T_1(x)$ the tax function for option 1 and $T_2(x)$ the
function for option 2.
  Using the appropriate stretches and translations to the tax function
$T(x)$, we get

  $$
  \answer{
  T_1(x)=\begin{cases}
  115 & x \leq 5\hspace{0.1em} 000 \\[6pt]
  1.15\left[\dfrac{(x-5\hspace{0.1em}000)^2}{50\hspace{0.1em}000}+100\right]  & 5\hspace{0.1em}000 <x \leq 15\hspace{0.1em}000 \\[9pt]
  1.15\left[\dfrac{1}{5}x-900\right] & 15\hspace{0.1em}000<x\\&
  \end{cases}
  }
  $$

  and

  $$
  \answer{
  T_2(x)=\begin{cases}
  0 & x \leq 5\hspace{0.1em} 000 \\[6pt]
  \dfrac{(1.4x-4\hspace{0.1em}000)^2}{50\hspace{0.1em}000}  & 5\hspace{0.1em}000 <x \leq 15\hspace{0.1em}000 \\[9pt]
  \dfrac{1.4x-4\hspace{0.1em}000}{5}\hspace*{1.92cm} & 15\hspace{0.1em}000<x\\&
  \end{cases}
  }
  $$

- Let the equation of the actual suspension cable be $f(x)$. Therefore, using both a vertical enlargement and horizontal enlargement of scale factor $\dfrac{1}{125}$ we have

  $$
  \begin{align*}
  h(x) = \dfrac{1}{125}\,f(125x)
  \end{align*}
  $$

  Expressing $f(x)$ in terms of $h(x)$ we have

  $$
  \begin{align*}
  f(x) &= 125\,h\left(\dfrac{x}{125}\right) \\[8pt]
  &= 125\left(\dfrac{7}{53}\left(\dfrac{x}{125}\right)^2 + 2\right) \\[8pt]
  &\hspace{-1.9em}\tcbhighmath{f(x) = 0.001057x^2 + 250\,,\,-575 \leq x \leq 575}
  \end{align*}
  $$

- The area required is given by the integral

  $$
  \begin{align*}
  A &= \displaystyle\int_{-575}^{575}\,0.001057x^2 + 250\,\mathrm{d}x \\[8pt]
  &\approx 421\,000\,\mathrm{cm}^2
  \end{align*}
  $$

  We can convert area in $\mathrm{cm}^2$ to area in $\mathrm{m}^2$ by dividing by $100^2$.
  The area bound by the vertical suspenders, the bridge deck and the suspension cable is approximately $42.1\,\text{m}{^2}$.
